---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Smeg Appliance Repair Los Angeles | FAB Refrigerator & Victoria Range Specialists";
const description = "Expert Smeg appliance repair in Los Angeles. FAB retro refrigerators, Victoria ranges, dishwashers — Italian-made since 1948. Same-day service, OEM parts. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Smeg Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-smeg-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "Smeg Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Smeg FAB Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Smeg Victoria Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Smeg Dishwasher Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Smeg Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Smeg Cooktop Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Smeg Coffee Machine Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Smeg appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Smeg repairs run $165–$520. FAB refrigerator thermostat, door gasket, or compressor service is on the lower-to-mid end. Dishwasher pump, oven control board, or range igniter work varies by model. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where are Smeg appliances made?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Smeg is made in Guastalla, in the Emilia-Romagna region of Italy — the same region known for Ferrari, Lamborghini, and Parmigiano-Reggiano. The company was founded in 1948 as Smalterie Metallurgiche Emiliane Guastalla. Every Smeg appliance is designed and engineered in Italy, with manufacturing centered in Guastalla."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair the Smeg FAB28 or FAB32 retro refrigerator?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The Smeg FAB series retro refrigerators are our most common Smeg service call in Los Angeles. The FAB28 and FAB32 use a modern sealed system and electronic controls beneath their iconic 1950s exterior. Common failures: thermostat drift, door gasket compression loss (the rounded door shape creates specific sealing requirements), and condenser fan motor failure. We carry FAB-specific gaskets and components."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are Smeg parts available in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — through Smeg's US distribution network. Smeg established a US-specific parts and service infrastructure to support the brand's strong American market presence. Common parts for FAB refrigerators, dishwashers, and ranges are typically available within 1–3 business days. Less common components may take longer given the Italian manufacturing source."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does my Smeg FAB refrigerator feel warm even when running?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The most common cause: condenser coil dust accumulation restricting airflow. Smeg FAB refrigerators are designed to be visually prominent in the kitchen, which often means placement in areas with reduced ventilation (against walls, in alcoves, in islands) that accelerates condenser dust loading. We check condenser clearance and coil condition before any sealed system diagnosis on every FAB refrigerator call."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service Smeg's Victoria range and colorful kitchen appliances?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — all Smeg cooking appliances including the Victoria series ranges, cooktops, and wall ovens. Smeg's colored enamel finishes require non-abrasive service protocols during any panel work. We apply protective covers and use enamel-safe cleaning agents on all colored Smeg surfaces as standard procedure."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .product-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .product-card { background: #161616; padding: 20px 18px; }
  .product-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .product-name { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .product-desc { font-size: 12px; color: #666; line-height: 1.55; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-italy { border-color: #2a5ea5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-italy .tip-label { color: #2a5ea5; }
  .tip-fab { border-color: #c8820a; background: #fff8f0; }
  .tip-fab .tip-label { color: #c8820a; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-fab { background: #c8820a; }
  .tag-color { background: #5a2a7a; }
  .tag-water { background: #2a5ea5; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .product-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Smeg Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Smeg Repair.<br/>
        <span>FAB. Victoria.</span><br/>
        Guastalla, Italy.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Smeg has been made in Guastalla, Emilia-Romagna since 1948. The FAB28 retro refrigerator, the Victoria range, the colored dishwashers that define a whole genre of design-forward kitchens in LA. We know the FAB's rounded door gasket geometry, the Victoria's enamel finish protocol, and how to source Italian parts without the wait. Same day across LA.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Smeg Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">FAB Refrigerator Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Victoria Range Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Enamel Finish Safe Protocol</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Smeg</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Guastalla, Emilia-Romagna. Italian-Made Since 1948.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Smeg — Smalterie Metallurgiche Emiliane Guastalla — was founded in 1948 in the town of Guastalla in Italy's Emilia-Romagna region. The same northern Italian region that gave the world Ferrari, Lamborghini, and Parmigiano-Reggiano also produced one of the world's most recognizable appliance brands. Smeg's engineering and design headquarters remain in Guastalla, where each product is developed with the dual mandate that defined the brand from the beginning: serious appliance performance expressed through design that earns a place in the room.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      In Los Angeles, Smeg occupies a specific and devoted market position. The FAB28 and FAB32 retro refrigerators are among the most photographed kitchen appliances on social media — they're as much a design statement as a functioning appliance. The Victoria series ranges bring the same Italian retro-modern aesthetic to cooking. Smeg dishwashers, available in ten-plus colors, define the design-forward kitchen in West Hollywood, Silver Lake, and Venice. These appliances are chosen deliberately, for specific reasons. Service should reflect that.
    </p>

    <div class="product-grid">
      <div class="product-card">
        <div class="product-icon">🧊</div>
        <div class="product-name">FAB Series Refrigerators</div>
        <div class="product-desc">The iconic retro-style refrigerators — FAB28 (50cm wide) and FAB32 (60cm wide) in 20+ colors and finishes. Curved retro exterior with modern sealed system and electronic controls inside. Available in right or left-hand door orientation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-card">
        <div class="product-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="product-name">Victoria Series Ranges</div>
        <div class="product-desc">Smeg's flagship cooking range — gas, dual-fuel, and induction configurations in 90cm and 120cm widths. Vintage-inspired knobs and handles, colored enamel finishes, five-burner gas with cast iron grates. The signature cooking appliance of the Smeg lineup.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-card">
        <div class="product-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="product-name">Dishwashers</div>
        <div class="product-desc">Smeg's freestanding and semi-integrated dishwashers in matching color families — coordinated with FAB refrigerators and Victoria ranges. Available in cream, pastel blue, pastel green, red, black, and more. Strong seller in LA's design-conscious kitchens.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-card">
        <div class="product-icon">☕</div>
        <div class="product-name">Small Appliances</div>
        <div class="product-desc">Smeg's expanding small appliance lineup — retro toasters, kettles, stand mixers, and espresso machines in matching color families. The most collectible Smeg category for LA design enthusiasts.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-card">
        <div class="product-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="product-name">Wall Ovens &amp; Cooktops</div>
        <div class="product-desc">Built-in gas and electric wall ovens, gas and induction cooktops — coordinated with the Victoria range aesthetic. Stainless and colored enamel options. Available in both standard and Dolce Stil Novo (collaboration) lines.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-card">
        <div class="product-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="product-name">Column &amp; Built-In Refrigerators</div>
        <div class="product-desc">Beyond the iconic FAB line — Smeg also makes panel-ready column refrigerators for flush cabinetry integration. These share component families with the standard Smeg refrigerator line but have different installation requirements.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-italy" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🇮🇹 Italian Parts — What to Expect</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Smeg appliances are engineered and manufactured in Italy, which means component sourcing flows through Smeg's Italian manufacturing chain. For the most common Smeg failures — FAB refrigerator door gaskets, thermostat components, dishwasher pumps, igniter assemblies — Smeg's US distribution maintains a local parts inventory that typically provides 1–3 day delivery. For less common components, the Italian source means longer lead times than domestic brands. We always check US stock availability before quoting turnaround on any Smeg repair, and we'll tell you honestly when a part requires international sourcing.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Smeg Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All Smeg models — FAB series, Victoria ranges, dishwashers, wall ovens, cooktops. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🧊</div>
        <div class="service-name">FAB Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">The Smeg FAB28 and FAB32 are LA's most recognizable retro refrigerators — and our most frequent Smeg service call. Beneath the iconic curved 1950s exterior is a modern sealed system with electronic temperature controls and a thermostat-managed compressor. The FAB's distinctive rounded door creates a specific gasket sealing geometry: the curved door profile requires a gasket that maintains compression around a compound curve, not a flat perimeter. When the FAB gasket fails, the door appears closed but air infiltration raises internal temperature without obvious symptoms.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: FAB door gasket (curved geometry) · not cooling · thermostat drift · compressor · condenser fan · temperature sensor · door hinge · handle hardware · evaporator defrost</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Victoria Range Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Smeg's Victoria series ranges — 90cm and 120cm configurations in gas, dual-fuel, and induction. Five sealed gas burners with cast iron grates, triple-glazed oven door, and the colored enamel body that defines the product. Enamel finish service protocol applies throughout: non-abrasive tools and cleaning agents, protective covers on all enamel panels during any service work. The cast iron grates require periodic re-seasoning at coastal LA properties.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: igniter failure · gas valve · oven temperature · convection fan · door gasket · control board · enamel finish protocol · cast iron grate re-seasoning (coastal) · LA hard water steam service</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Dishwasher Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Smeg's freestanding and semi-integrated dishwashers. Smeg dishwashers in LA are often chosen for color coordination with FAB refrigerators — a Pastel Blue Smeg dishwasher next to a Pastel Blue FAB28 is a specific design choice that makes the appliance impossible to replace without ruining the kitchen concept. We approach Smeg dishwasher repairs with awareness of the finish continuity — no scratches on the colored door panels. LA hard water scale in the spray circuit is addressed on every Smeg dishwasher service call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not draining · not cleaning · door latch · pump motor · spray arm scale · control board · water inlet · door gasket · color finish protocol · heating element</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven &amp; Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Smeg built-in wall ovens and cooktops — gas and induction. The Dolce Stil Novo collection (Smeg's higher-end line) uses a distraction-free design with touch controls and specific electronics. Smeg's induction cooktops share the European-designed inverter architecture found in other Italian brands — zone-specific inverter faults present differently than US-manufactured induction. We diagnose Smeg induction at the inverter level before any surface or glass assessment.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: temperature sensor · heating element · convection fan · oven not heating · induction zone fault · door gasket · control board · touch control fault · Dolce Stil Novo electronics</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">☕</div>
        <div class="service-name">Coffee Machine Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Smeg's retro espresso machines and drip coffee makers — the BCC02 and ECF01 are among the most popular Smeg products in LA design kitchens. LA hard water at 250–400 ppm builds scale in espresso machine boilers and group heads faster than Smeg's standard descaling interval assumes — we address scale as the first diagnosis on every Smeg coffee machine call. Smeg coffee machines use European-engineered pumps and boilers that are serviceable as components.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: scale buildup (LA water) · pump failure · boiler fault · not brewing · temperature inconsistency · steam wand fault · gasket · descaling service + interval reset</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">✨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Colored Enamel Finish Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Smeg's colored enamel and retro finishes — Pastel Blue, Cream, Red, Black, Pastel Green, and the specialty collections — require non-abrasive service protocols. Enamel chips at sharp impact and cannot be touched up without professional respray. Unlike stainless steel (which hides minor contact), Smeg's colors show any service contact mark immediately. We apply protective covers to all colored surfaces before service and use only enamel-safe cleaning agents throughout.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">All standard repairs with enamel-safe cleaning agents, protective covers, and visual finish confirmation before and after every service visit. Color-coordinated parts ordering when exterior components need replacement.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-fab" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🧊 FAB Refrigerator — The Gasket Geometry Nobody Explains</div>
      <div class="tip-text">The Smeg FAB refrigerator's rounded door is its defining visual feature — and its primary service consideration. The curved door profile requires a gasket that maintains compression around a compound curve rather than the flat perimeter of a standard refrigerator door. A standard refrigerator gasket replacement technique doesn't apply: the FAB gasket must be fitted with awareness of the radius changes around the door's corners and sides. When installed incorrectly, the gasket appears sealed visually but allows air infiltration at the compound-curve sections. We use FAB-specific gasket installation technique on every Smeg FAB door seal call — and we verify seal integrity with a paper test around the full door perimeter before the job is complete.</div>
