        <div class="problem-cause">Two distinct causes, both common. FAB door gasket failure at the compound-curve corners — air infiltration raises interior temperature gradually. FAB condenser coil dust accumulation from placement against walls or in alcoves. We check both before sealed system diagnosis: paper test for gasket integrity around the full FAB perimeter, and condenser clearance + coil condition before any refrigerant work.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-fab">FAB Refrigerator</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Victoria Igniter Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Smeg Victoria's sealed burner igniters are Italian-spec components — ceramic tip geometry specific to the burner configuration. Coastal LA salt air accelerates ceramic corrosion. Generic igniters at incorrect geometry produce weak spark even when new. OEM Smeg Victoria igniters only. We inspect all burner igniter tips on coastal Victoria service calls.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍽️ Dishwasher Not Draining + Scale</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Drain pump blockage combined with LA hard water scale accumulation in the spray circuit — two simultaneous issues that share one service call. LA water at 250–400 ppm builds scale in Smeg dishwasher spray arms and filters faster than Smeg's European-calibrated maintenance intervals assume. We address both the mechanical blockage and the scale simultaneously on every Smeg dishwasher call.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-water">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">☕ Espresso Machine Scale Buildup</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Scale accumulation in the boiler and group head — LA water hardness at 250–400 ppm is 2–3× harder than the European baseline Smeg's standard descaling interval assumes. "Not brewing properly" and "weak pressure" on Smeg coffee machines are almost always scale, not pump failure. We perform deep descale and reset the descaling reminder to LA water hardness on every Smeg coffee machine call.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-water">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Inconsistency</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Temperature sensor drift — Smeg ovens use Italian-spec temperature sensors with European calibration. Many temperature issues are calibration offsets rather than sensor failures — adjustable through the service menu without parts. We test with a calibrated probe at multiple setpoints before ordering any sensor. Calibration adjustment costs a fraction of sensor replacement and resolves a significant portion of Smeg oven temperature complaints.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

